Sales of beverages are expressed in unit case volume. A “unit case” means a unit of measurement
equal to 192 U.S. fluid ounces of finished beverage (24 eight-ounce servings). Unit case volume means the
number of unit cases (or unit case equivalents) of finished products or concentrates, as if converted into
finished products, sold by us.
