demand in the warmer months of the year. It has been our experience that beverage sales tend to be lower
during the first and fourth quarters of each calendar year. In addition, our experience with our energy drink
products suggests they are less seasonal than the seasonality expected from traditional beverages. Quarterly
fluctuations may also be affected by other factors including the introduction of new products, the opening
of new markets where temperature fluctuations are more pronounced, the addition of new
bottlers/distributors and customers, changes in the sales mix of our products and changes in and/or
increased advertising and promotional expenses. (See “Part I, Item 1 – Business – Seasonality”).
